The paper deals with a computer vision problem of human pose estimation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of a neural network, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the model involves analyzing performance metrics, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
